data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer takes an expression tree

EF Core 10 changed the signature from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Action<...>`. Your manual expression-tree construction won't compile. The fix is dramatically simpler:

```csharp
// EF Core 10 — just use a regular lambda
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, etc. — conditional logic goes directly in the lambda body.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two sub-issues

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF will append a number to disambiguate (e.g., `Street1`). This generates a column-rename migration.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin column names explicitly to prevent renames:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    {
        // logCommandText contains redacted SQL (safe for logging)
        // command.CommandText contains the actual SQL
    }
}
```

Apply the same change to every method on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
